result.execSummary:
The defendant Denise L Daniels was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct w/motor vehicle. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Called at 9:50 AM. Denise Daniels appears in person and with counsel Gary Cirilli. State appears by Charles Simono. State - here on a voluntary appearance. Court makes statement regarding setting matters for voluntary appearances twice in this matter. Cirilli responds - explains why the defendant was not here last week. Court will quash the warrant. Cirilli waiving right to PH, provides court with waiver of PH form. Court goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived her right to PH, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. State has filed Information that mirrors the complaint. Cirilli has Information, waives reading of it, will proceed to ARGN and pleads NG to all counts. Court accepts plea, reinstates signature bond previously ordered, set for FPT on 10/22/14 at 2:15 PM, warns the defendant of non-appearance and late appearances again.

Called at 2:41 PM. Denise Daniels does not appear but her attorney Gary Cirilli is present. State appears by Charles Simono. State - several offices have received calls from the defendant today that she will not be appearing today due to medical appointments, believe that Cirilli was waiving the PH for today, are very close to resolution. Cirilli agrees. State - asks for bench warrant. Cirilli - asks court to schedule for an ARGN/FPT. Court forfeits bond, issues bench warrant, body or $1500.00.
